chapter.para:
On the topic of linking, there are three types of links you want to use.  The first has already been demonstrated, an "xref".  It points to a block which has an ID.  It then uses the "title" child of that block as the text displayed for the reference.  If you do not want to use the text provided, you can use a simple link where you provide the text.  I don't recommend it, as it makes maintenence harder if we rename stuff.



    Before I forget, you can use a shorthand notation to refer to the product itself.  For example,  plug in your ⪚.  It is the literal &eg;


The last type of link is a link to the glossary.  Unfortunatly, it doesn't seem to pick-up the term from the glossary so you need to add it.  For example, here is a link to SMTP.  You'll likely be referring to a lot of terms which are already in the glossary.  If you need to add a term, I'm sure you can figure out the pattern.
